  "text": "In 2015, Sloane et al. [CITATION_1] used a tailored lighting intervention that delivered more short-wavelength content and reduced the light levels to 17 pairs of ADRD patients and caregivers living at home. In a crossover, within-subjects design, subjects received a tailored and a placebo light in living spaces where they were most likely to spend their time during the day. Subjects experienced each condition for six weeks, separated by a four-week washout period. The tailored lighting intervention did not significantly affect actigraphic and self-reports of sleep measures in ADRD patients, but it did improve sleep and reduced strain in caregivers.",
